ttp://dbpedia.org/resource/BAFTA_Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/BAFTA_Scotland" target="_blank">BAFTA</a> awardHe won for his role in short film Happy Together the story of a homeless youth who forms a close <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Bond" target="_blank">bond</a> with a lonely old woman Ikunda posed grinning with <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Mullan" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Mullan" target="_blank">Peter Mullan</a> at the ceremony and will  soon be starring alongside him in  Hec McAdam a road movie about a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homelessness" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Homelessness" target="_blank">homeless</a> man from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/BAFTA_Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/BAFTA_Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a> who heads for <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" target="_blank">London</a> He told the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interview" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interview" target="_blank">interviewer</a> â<a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Mullan" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Mullan" target="_blank">Peter Mullan</a> is a great guy We had a good time and I asked him a few questions and he gave me some adviceâHe added âActors like <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Mullan" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peter_Mullan" target="_blank">Peter</a> and James McAvoy inspire me because they have worked hard to get to where they are without a lot of help or moneyâIt's a difficult industry to break into but I write <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Screenplay" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Screenplay" target="_blank">screenplays</a> too just in case Basically I'm writing myself a jobâYou sit on the sidelines waiting for parts that don't come that often And when they do you have a roomful of people doing the same thing You have to work hard but I'm willing to do thatâAstonishingly Ikunda also claimed in the <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interview" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Interview" target="_blank">interview</a> that he moved to <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Glasgow" target="_blank">Glasgow</a> from <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" target="_blank">London</a> to escape a life of crimeHis parents fled to the UK capital from the wartorn Democratic Republic of CongoBut Ikunda said âI had to leave <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" target="_blank">London</a> The peer pressure and environment wasn't goodâThere's a <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gang" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gang" target="_blank">gang culture</a> there and you can get mixed up in things young boys shouldn't get mixed up inâSome of the boys I went to school with now have criminal records I could have been one of those boys I didn't want to leave <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/London" target="_blank">London</a> but maybe it was a blessing in disguiseâIkunda also claimed that being black made it hard for him to make friends in GlasgowHe said âIt was like going to this area where you were more like a display in the museum Everybody is looking at you like a walking tourist attractionâI kind of lost touch with <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acting" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acting" target="_blank">acting</a> to begin with because I was just trying to adjust to living in <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/BAFTA_Scotland" title="http://dbpedia.org/resource/BAFTA_Scotland" target="_blank">Scotland</a>âI already felt separated because I was black and I thought showing my passion for <a href="http://dbpedia.org/resource/Acting" title="h